Together with {{ill|Tōdaisha|ja|東大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Toyotama-hime Shrine (Katori)|ja|豊玉姫神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, Raijin Shrine hosts a {{ill|shikinen shinkōsai|ja|式年神幸祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} every 20 years. The "Kurahashi no Miroku Sambasō" dance, performed as a forerunner to the portable shrine procession, is considered a form of {{ill|Kashima Odori|ja|鹿島踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. Its unique formation of dancers moving in a line has led to its designation as an {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.

== Access ==

* 15-minute walk from {{ill|Kurahashi Station|ja|倉橋駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Sōbu Main Line|ja|総武本線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, operated by {{ill|JR East|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.

